						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 90 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp with an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee a day in the temple of Mahādēva at Tirumaṟaikkāḍu by one <hi rend="bold">Sāmanāyaka-Perumāḷ Tukki of Vēṭṭaivayal.</hi> Mention is made of a liquid measure called <hi rend="italic">Tirumaṟaikāḍaṉ</hi> after the god.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
